Length ball but down leg, Warner looks to tuck it but fails to get any wood on the ball.
Length and around middle, tucked towards mid-wicket by Warner off the back foot.
FOUR! Pulled away! Short and around off, Warner is happy as it sits perfectly for him. He pulls it through square leg and fetches yet another boundary.
Good comeback from Thakur. Bowls another short one but Warner this time drops his wrists and lets the ball sway away from him.
Length ball on the pads, tucked away towards square leg for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally, India and Thakur get the breakthrough they needed. Thakur is elated and why wouldn't he be? He has been bowling superbly and deserves this wicket. Bowls a short one around middle, Harris sits in response but fails to take his gloves out of the line of the ball. The ball brushes his gloves and goes to the keeper. Pant there accepts the catch gleefully as Thakur appeals to see the umpire raise his finger. A wicket down as Australia are effectively 122/1!
BEATEN! Tossed up ball around off, Warner lunges forward to defend but is beaten on the outside edge there.
Flatter and on off, Warner punches it to covers.
Floated around off, Warner drives it a bit uppish through covers and manages a couple this time.
On off, pushed to mid on this time by Warner.
Flatter and around off, blocked.

OUT! LBW! One brings two as the saying goes. It has happened here too. THREE REDS! WARNER DEPARTS AND TAKES THE REVIEW TOO! Sundar has been brilliant in this game as he gets a wicket in this innings too. Tosses this one up on off, and gets it to straighten off the surface, Warner tries to play it off the back foot but he fails to get bat on the ball. The ball thuds him on the pads and the appeal from Washington leads the umpire to raise his dreaded finger. Warner initially decides to walk off without reviewing but he is coaxed by Labuschagne to take the review. Just at the last instance before the timer went off he signals 'T'. Replays roll in and there is no spot on the Hot Spot and the RTS fails to pick any nick when the ball is near the bat. Then comes the Ball Tracker and it shows to be three reds as Warner keeps walking off the field.
Good length and around off, blocked.
Just outside off on a good length, Labuschagne lets it alone.
Short ball on middle, Labuschagne pulls but finds square leg.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Wide outside off, left alone again.
Labuschagne is off the mark. Fullish and around off, it is tucked towards mid-wicket for a quick single.
Flatter and around middle, tucked on the leg side.
Shortish and just outside off, cut well but straight to point.
FOUR! Nicely done! Flatter and outside off, Marnus rocks back and manages to guide it through short third man for a boundary.
Tossed up and around middle, clipped towards the leg side for a single.

Smith shows signs of aggression on the first ball. A loopy ball around middle, Smith jumps out of his crease and flicks it over mid-wicket. Saini, struggling with his injury is not the quickest to get to the ball and that allows them to take three. 100 up for the Aussies. The lead now reads 133.
Tossed up ad around off, swept well but straight to square leg.
Fullish and around off, blocked.
Another three runs for Smith! Full and angled on the pads, Smith clips it in front of square on the leg side and gets three easily as the fielder in the deep does the mopping up.
Short and around middle, Labuschagne lets it go through as he ducks.

FOUR! Brilliant effort but Saini fails to prevent the four! Thakur bowls a fuller one on middle, Labuschagne drives it off the front foot through mid on. Saini who is nurturing a groin strain chases the ball till the end. At the first instance it looks like he has saved a certain boundary but the umpires go for a check.
Shortish and around off, poked towards point.
FOUR! Easy for Labuschagne! A big over for the Aussies. Shardul strays on the pads. Marnus just clips it down to the fine leg fence. 11 off the over.
Full and around middle, Smith clips it to the leg side and takes a quick single on offer.
Tosed up on off, kept out from within the crease.
Flatter and around off, Labuschagne guides it through short third man and gets a couple by the time the ball is fielded near the ropes.
FOUR! Over the top! Tossed up on midlde, Labuschagne lofts it over mid on and gets a boundary at long on this time. THE LEAD GOES ON TO 152 RUNS!
Floated on leg, clipped towards square leg for a single.
Flatter and going down leg as Smith plays the short arm jab straight to the man at square leg. 8 runs off the over.
Shorter and outside off, Labuschagne slashes at it but finds point.
FOUR! Deliberately done! Runs are flowing once again. Length and outside off, Labuschagne guides it past the slip and into the third man fence for a boundary.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Siraj deserved that wicket, Nice line, nice length and Labuschagne fails to negotiate. The centurion from the first innings departs this time for 25. Bowls it fast and straight does Siraj as Labuschagne looks to play it off the back foot. The ball is travelling at a good height there as Labuschagne tries to play it away from his body. The ball takes the outside edge and flies to the second slip where Rohit holds onto it. Rahane's move to bring Siraj back into the attack pays off.
Length and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
On off, kept out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Strangled down the leg this time! India fighting back again, after a blistering first hour from Australia. Siraj gets his second of the over. A nothing delivery but as far as it fetches a wicket India won't mind. Wade departs without troubling the scorers. Length and down the leg side. Wade shuffles across to off, to tuck it to the leg side but what he could manage is just a faint edge. Which goes at a good height to Pant who dives to his right and takes it just inches above the ground.
On off, kept out from within the crease.
Floated on off, pushed to long on for a single.
A full toss on middle, Green pushes it to covers and goes searching for a single as he comes outside his crease but is sent well back in time by Smith there.
Tossed up on leg, tucked towards mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off driven through mid on for a single to get off the mark by Green.
Flatter and on off, punched through covers for a single.
Good length and around off, Smith looks to work it on the leg side but gets squared up slightly. The ball goes to point and they take one.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Outside off again, Green lets it be.
Slightly fullish and just outside off, Green covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
This time Siraj angles in from off and middle, it is clipped towards square leg.
Fullish and around off, a solid front foot block from Green.
Very full and aroud off, pushed to the right side of the bowler. Sundar fumbles but they don't take run.
Ouch! That was swept powerfully. Tossed up and outside off, Smith nails the sweep. However, it hits the leg of the short leg fielder. Mayank is the man there, he looks in pain.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed towards point.
Flatter and around off, turning in. It is tucked down to fine leg for one.
Full and around off, pushed to mid off for a quick run.
Full and on middle, clipped to deep mid-wicket for one.
Good length and around off, kept out.
Back of a length and around off and middle, Smith looks to pull but misses to get hit on the body.
Shortish and just around off, Smith punches it well but finds the cover fielder.
Back of a length and just outside off, punched well again but straight to the fielder again.
Good length and around off, Smith works it towards the leg side.
Maiden from Siraj. The last ball is fulish and around off, Smith plays is towards mid off.
Good length and around off from Saini to begin. Green pushes it back to the bowler.
Shortish and around off, Green looks to defend but the ball takes the outer half and goes to point.
Around off on a length, pushed towards the cover region.
Fuller and around off, driven straight to mid off by Green.
Saini goes little wide outside off, Green lets it be.
A maiden from Saini. Top effort from the man who is not 100 percent fit. Shortish and just outside off, pushed on the off side for nothing.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Landed around off, pushed towards mid on.
Banged short and on middle, pulled down to fine leg for one.
Fullish and around off, stroked to mid on for nothing.
Length and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Dot to end! It is another tight over from the Indians. Length ball around off, it is tucked towards mid-wicket for nothing.

FOUR! Slashed! Smith is carrying the form from the first innings. Remember he got out after getting set in the first innings. This one is bowled well wide outside off and on short of good length area. Smith throws the kitchen sink at it to send it off the outside edge over the gully region and into the fence at third man.

Play and a miss this time. Lovely from Saini. He is not at his best but beats the outside edge of Smith. Pitches around the shrotish length and around off, it shapes away as Smith looks to defend but is beaten.
Length ball around off, defended.
Full and on the pads, Smith flicks it through mid-wicket for one. Wanted two but decides against it.
Length and around off, poked towards point.
Good length and around middle, clipped wide of the man at mid on for one.
Length and outside off, Green makes a leave first up.
Length and well going down leg, Green looks to play it to the fine leg area but misses it altogether.

NOT OUT! IMPACT IS UMPIRE'S CALL! GREEN SURVIVES AND INDIA DO NOT LOSE A REVIEW! Full and sliding onto middle and leg, Green looks to flick it off the front foot but is beaten to get hit right on the knee roll. Natarajan goes up in appeal so does his teamanates but the umpire is unmoved. Rahane after thinking for a while goes for the revive. Nothing on the HotSpot and RTS. Ball Tracker shows impact umpire's call and wickets too were missing. Green stays on for now.
Length and on off, watchfully kept out by Green.
Angled in from just outside off, Green looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pad again.
A maiden from Natarajan. Testing over for Green. The last ball is around off on a length, Green gets behind the line of the ball to block.
Full and on middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a brace. Saini oversteps.
Length and on off, played back to the bowler.
Length and outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Poor ball and it gets the treatment. Short and on middle and leg. Smith moves inside the crease and thumps it down to the fine leg fence.
Outside off, left alone this time.

Huge appeal but not out says the umpire. No review from the Indians. This one was angled in from outside off, Smith didn't cover the inward movement and shouldered arms. The ball came back in sharply and hit his pad. They appealed but turned down by the umpire.
Good length and around off, Smith is solid in defense.
Length and outside off, Green comes on the front foot and then makes a leave.
On a length and on off, Green taps it towards mid on and takes a single.
FOUR! Smith's merry ways continue! Short of good length but not that short to execute a pull but Smith still goes ahead with his shot as he nails it in the gap at mid-wicket for a boundary.
Full and on off, Smith defends it off the back foot.
Full and on off, pushed to mid on off theÂ  back foot once again by Smith.
Fuller and on off, Smith guides it to point where the substitute Prithvi Shaw fields it. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY4!
Good leave! Close leave. Good start from Shardul. This one pitches just outside off, hits a crack and comes back in. Green covers his stumps and lets it be.
Gets behind the line of the ball this time to defend.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Fuller and around middle, stroked straight to mid on.
Just outside off on a good length. Another leave from Green.
Maiden from Thakur to begin the new session. The last ball is wide outside off, so Green leaves it alone again.
Full and on the pads, Smith flicks it through to fine leg. A couple taken in the end. 150 comes up for Australia.
Length and on off, pushed to mid on.
Length and down the leg, left alone.
Another one going down leg, easy leave for Smith there.
Fuller and on middle, Smith strokes it straight towards mid-wicket.
A single to end the over! Full and on leg, clipped towards fine leg by Smith.
Length and on off, turned towards mid on this time by Smith.
Length and on off, pushed to mid off from within the crease.
Short and wide outside off, slapped through point for a single as there is protection in the deep there.
Length and on off, punched off the back foot towards the bowler by Green.
Length and outside off, Green punched it crisply towards covers to find the fielder there.
BEATEN! Length and outside off, Green looks to punch it from within the crease but ends up missing it altogether as the ball goes past his outside edge.
Short of good length on off, Smith punched it straight to the cover fielder.
Fuller on leg, Smith plays it to mid on. Natarajan oversteps! NO BALL CALLED!
Full and on middle, clipped towards mid-wicket by Smith there.
Another one angled into off and middle, Smith turns it off the front foot towards mid-wicket once again.
Another full ball on the pads, Smith flicks it straight to square leg this time.
Full and on off, Smith blocks it right from within the crease.
In the air...Just short! Full and on leg, Smith clips it uppishly towards square leg where it falls just short of Rohit Sharma. Lucky there is Smith.
Full and on middle, clipped to the leg side for a single.
FOUR! Hammered! Short and outside off, Smith pulls it and gets it towards mid-wicket as the ball meets the fence.
Fuller and on middle, clipped towards mid-wicket for a single.
Length and around off, defended off the back foot by Green.
Another fuller length ball on off, pushed down the ground off the back foot. Shardul too slips in his followthrough there.
Length and on midlde, clipped towards mid-wicket by Green for a single as he keeps the strike for the next over.
Fuller and outside off, pushed wide of the man at mid off for one.
Good length and around off, pushed towards the off side.
Full and around off, Smith drops it in front of the cover fielder for a quick run.
Fullish and outside off, Green drives it through backward point and gets three. The lead reads 199 now.
Around off on a length, kept out.
Full and just outside off, driven to mid off for nothing.
Full and on the pads, Green comes down the track and looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. A mild appeal.
Floated on middle and leg, it turns in as Green lets it be. Pant does well to move to his left to collect.
Full and on the pads, flicked to square leg.
Full and on middle, this time Green flicks it wide of the man at long on. Two taken and the lead goes over 200.
On the pads, clipped to the left of square leg fielder for one more.

FOUR! BOOM! Smith into the 40s now! Tossed up and around off, Smith makes room and dances down the ground. Gets to the pitch of the ball and nails the drive through mid off. Super shot. 50-run stand is also up between these two.
Length and around off, defended.
That kept really low. How did that ball miss the stumps. A length ball outside off, it hits the crack and keeps low. Green looks to defend but misses.
Length and around off, Green looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the pad.
Appeal for LBW but that looked to be going down the leg side. Angled in from around off, Green looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. They appeal but not out says the umpire.
Green gets another blow on the body. This one pitches and comes back in again. It bounces extra to beat the bat. Green gets hit near the box.
Manages to work the last ball towards mid-wicket. A testing over.

DROPPED AND FOUR! How costly will that be? A tossed up ball around off, Smith jumps out of his crease and looks to go downtown. He mistimes it towards long on where Siraj misjudges the catch. Gets both hands but it pops out and goes to the fence. Sundar cannot believe it.
Fired on middle, Smith looks to paddle it down the leg side but misses. The keeper fails to collect and they take a bye.
Flatter and around off, kept out.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Flat and around off, Green comes down the track and pushes it towards the bowler.
Flatter and around off, Green goes back to block.
Shot! Shortish and just outside off, Smith punches it to the left of the cover fielder. The fielder dives to his left but fails to stop. Three more for Smith. He moves to 49.
Fullish and around off, blocked to mid on.
Shortish and just outside off, kept out.
Banged short and down the leg side. Green looks to bang it on the leg side but makes no connection.
Length ball around off, pushed to mid on.
Angled in from around off and middle, Green looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball goes to fine leg. They take two leg byes.
Tossed up and around off, played to mid on.
Full and around off, played back to the bowler.
FIFTY FOR SMITH! A fine knock that has come at a brisk pace. Shortish and around middle, tucks around the corner for a single. His 31st half ton in the format.
On off, pushed to mid off for a quick single.
Flatter and around middle, tucked on the leg side for nothing.
Flat and around off, Smith works it towards square leg again.
Length and on middle, clipped towards square leg for a dot.
BEATEN! Length and outside off, Green looks to defend it out but is beaten on the outside edge.
Full and on off, driven straight to the point fielder.

DROPPED! Siraj drops one off his own bowling this time. Green gets a life. Full and straight on off, Green strokes it straight down the ground. It is a bit uppish as Siraj goes for the catch but ends up spilling it. That should have been taken. How costly would the drop of Green prove for India?
Length and around off, pushed to mid on.
Just outside off on a good length, blocked.
Flatter and around off, blocked.
EDGED AND FOUR! Tossed up around off, Smith looks to go for the drive but ends up getting a thick outside edge. The ball rolls towards the third man region as it crosses the fence there.
On middle, clipped towards the leg side for a single.
Fuller and around middle, flicked to silly mid on.
Flatter and just outside off, Green manages to push it towards third man for a brace.
FOUR! Tossed up and outside off, Green sweeps it and finds the fence at deep square leg.
Fullish and around off, kept out.

OUT! TAKEN! The glove is in the cotact of the bat and Smith has to go. He wasn't sure about it and hence went for the review. A lovely ball from Siraj. A length ball around off, this one shoots off after hitting the deck. Smith fends at it awkardly. The ball hits his gloves and goes to the left of Rahane at gully. The Indian skipper is not going to drop it. The Indians celebrate. Smith has a word with his partner at the other end. He is suggesting that maybe his hand was off the glove when the ball kissed it. And hence he goes for the review. Replays roll in and they show otherwise. So, the onfield call will stay. Siraj's twin drops doesn't cost India much. A fine knock from Smith comes to an end.
Fullish and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Another cobra from Siraj. It hits the crack and bounces extra. Paine is not sure how to play at it. Manages to fend it off towards the off side.
Length ball around off, kept out.
Fuller and around off, Paine pushes it back to Siraj. A wicket maiden from him.
Tossed up and around off, kept out.
Full and on middle, stroked to long on for one.
Paine is underway! Flat and around middle and leg, Paine clips it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Flat and around off, poked towards point.
Full and around off, Green comes back and blocks back to the bowler.
FOUR! Swept and swept well. Tossed up and outside off, Green drags the ball from there and sends it past the square leg fielder and into the fence.
Full and around off, Paine pushes it to the left of the cover fielder for a single.
Shortish and around off, it is tapped in front of the point fielder for one.
Full and on middle, pushed to mid on for nothing.
On the pads this time. Paine tucks it towards fine leg for a run.
Good shot but for no run. Full and outside off, Green drives it hard but finds mid off.
Full and wide outside off, Green drives it hard towards the right side of the cover fielder who dives and makes a half stop. A single.
Length ball around off, it is flicked through mid-wicket for a brace.
FOUR! Poor from Saini. He offers width and bowls it short too. Green slams it through backward point for a boundary.
Short and around off, tapped on the off side for a quick run.
Length and around off, Paine pushes it towards mid on.
Good length and around middle, Paine looks to work it on the leg side but he misses to get hit on the thigh pad.

Shot! Full and on middle, Paine flicks it past mid on. The fielder dives to his right to stop but misses. Has to get up and return to the keeper by chasing it near the fence. That allows the batters to take three. 10 from the over, a good one for the Aussies. The lead is now 249.
Back of a length and around off, pushed towards point off the toes.
Short and wide outside off, Paine punches it well but straight to the point fielder.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, Paine makes another leave.
Short and around middle, Paine tucks it wide of the man at mid on for a single. The lead reaches 250 runs!
Banged short and on middle and leg, Green sits under it.
Full and around off, stroked to mid off for nothing.
Back of a length and on middle, Paine clips it through square leg for a run.
Shortish and around off, played back to the bowler.
Three more! Runs coming fast for the Aussies again. A fullish ball around off, Green drives it through mid on. Sundar gives it a chase and dives to make a stop. Saves a run for the side.
FOUR! Down the ground again. This time it is Paine. Just forces it through mid on and this time Sundar is not chasing it. 8 off the over already.
A single and it is 9 off it now. Short and just outside off, punched down to deep point for a single. Another expensive over from Saini. He is leaking runs here.
A fuller ball around off and middle to begin, Paine flicks it uppishly. It is to the right of Gill but it just falls short.

Quick single! Direct hit would've made things a bit interesting. A fuller ball around off, Paine pushes it towards mid off and goes for a risky run. The fielder there has a shy at the non-striker's end but he misses.
Back of a length and around off, kept out.
Length and around off, blocked towards mid on this time.

OUT! TAKEN AT SECOND SLIP! Lovely bowling from Shardul. Lands the length ball just around off, Green pokes at it away from his body as the ball bounces extra. It takes the outside edge and goes to the right of Rohit. The Indian opener takes the chance easily. 5th catch for him in this game. End of a battling knock for Green.
In the channel outside off, Cummins leaves it alone. End of a successful over for Shardul.
Tossed up on off, pushed back down the ground towards long on for a single.
Flaoted on off, pushed to covers by Cummins who looks to get off the mark but is sent back by Paine.
Fuller and on off, whipped past the short mid-wicket fielder for a couple of runs. Cummins off the mark.
Floated down leg, Cummins does not fiddle with it.
Flighted on off, Cummins manages to keep it away to the off side off the back foot.
Beaten! Darted just around off, Cummins looks to defend it off his back foot but fails to connect.
SHOT! Full and around off, Paine plays a handsome cover drive but fails to get it past the fielder there.
Short of good length around off, Paine punched it off the back foot through covers for a single.
Length and outside off, Cummins shoulders arms to it.
Fuller and outside off, Cummins does not disturb the path of the ball there as he lets it go through to the keeper.
Full and on midlde, clipped towards mid-wicket off the back foot by Cummins.
Length and down leg, wayward from Thakur as Cummins goes for the pull only to miss it. Pant does well to get it off one-hand by running to his left.
Tossed up on off, Paine misses his tuck as the ball hits his pads. There is an appeal but nothing from the umpire.
FOUR! Flicked away! Tossed up on leg, Paine just tickles it fine towards fine leg as the ball goes onto meet the fence there.
FOUR! Innovative from Paine! Sundar tosses it up and and bowls it on middle, Paine brings out the reverse sweep. Nails it through point and finds consecutive boundaries.
Tossed up on leg, spinning down leg, left alone.
Turning in from just outside off, Paine looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad.
Paine looks to make room. Sundar follows him. Paine manages to force it towards deep point for a single.
Length and on off, kept out from the crease by Paine.
Length and outside off, Paine lets it be this time.
Short and outside off, slapped through covers for a couple.
Good length and around off, Paine blocks it out.
Fuller and on off, Paine gets low to push this one towards mid on this time.

OUT! CAUGHT! A sharp catch from Rishabh Pant there. Thakur picks up his third. A short around off, Paine swivels to pull but ends up getting a top edge which goes towards Pant who takes the catch over his head. He timed the jump to perfection there. Takes it and jumps in jubilation. Shardul is pumped as well. The lead is now 275 runs!
EDGED BUT WELL SHORT! Length and around off, Cummins looks to defend it out off the back goot but the ball takes the outside edge and drops short of the first slip fielder.
On middle, clipped towards mid-wicket.
Length and outside off, Cummins leaves it alone.
Full on off, driven straight to mid off from the front foot by Cummins.
Length and around off, blocked towards covers by Cummins from within the crease.
Lovely bowling! Length and around off, Cummins looks to have a feel of the ball as he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length and around middle, clipped behind square on the leg side for a single.
Starts with a bumper after resumption as Cummins sits under it.
Length and down leg, Cummins looks to tickle it fine but misses it.

FOUR! Throws the kitchen sink at it! Full and wide outside off, Cummins thows the bat at it to get an edge. The ball flies over the slips and into the fence at third man for a boundary. That is what is expected from the Australian tail.
Slower short ball on leg, Cummins sits under it. The ball though brushes back of his helmet a bit before going to the keeper.
Length and outside off, left alone by Cummins.
Shortish and around off, blocked.
Play and a miss! Fullish and outside off, going away. Starc throws the willow but makes no connection.

OUT! CAUGHT! Siraj removes Starc and gets his 4th here. A fuller ball outside off, Starc looks to hammer it over mid off but he ends up hitting it off the outer half. It goes to the left of Saini at mid off who moves that side and gobbles the catch easily. India just 2 away from bundling the Aussies.
Shot! What a shot from Lyon to get off the mark. A fuller ball around off, Lyon hits it through mid on and gets three. 250 up for the Aussies. The lead now goes to 283.
Short and wide outside off, Cummins cuts it hard but Rahane intercepts nicely at gully.
Edged but short! Length and around off, Cummins looks to defend but ends up getting an outside edge. The ball goes to second slip but falls well short. End of a successful over from Siraj.
Length ball around off, a solid front foot defense.
Fuller and around middle, clipped to long on for one.
Length and around off, played back to the bowler.
Shortish and just outside off, tapped to the left of deep cover for a brace.
Short ball around off, Pat pulls but finds mid on.
Banged short, Cummins manages to help it down to fine leg for a single.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards the cover region.

EDGY FOUR! Useful runs! Siraj lands this around off, maybe on one of those cracks. It came back in sharply. Smith looks to keep it out but it hits his elbow and races down to the fine leg fence, past his stumps. Runs given though.
Short and around off, pulled down to square leg for one. A slight fumble but they don't go for the run.
Full and around off, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Superb bouncer! Cummins does well to move out of the way.
WIDE! Another sharp bumper! Cummins sways away. The square leg umpire calls it wide.
Good length and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Banged short, Lyon pulls it down to deep square leg for one.
Another bouncer! Cummins decides not to take it on. He sits under it.
Looks to pull this time but makes no connection.
NO BALL! Short and wide outside off, Cummins lets it be. Called no ball.
Short and outside off, Cummins pulls and hits it through mid-wicket. Before long on can come around, they take three.
Play and a miss! Length ball outside off, Lyon looks to punch it on the up but he misses.
Fuller and around off, driven well but straight to mid off.
Full and outside off, Cummins drives but finds mid off.
A single now and the lead is 300 now. Length ball around off, it is pulled down to deep mid-wicket for a single.
SIX! Goes all the way! Superb from Lyon. Banged short and on middle, Lyon swivels and pulls it over fine leg for a biggie.
Low full toss, Lyon looks to drive but the ball takes the inner half and goes to square leg for a single.
Full and on off, Cummins swings hard but cannot beat the man at mid on.
BEATEN! Short of a good length around off, Cummins swings hard but can only connect with thin air.

OUT! CAUGHT! In the air and taken! That's wicket number 4 for Shardul Thakur. Short and around off, Lyon goes to swat it to the off side. But it hits the higher part of the bat and goes towards covers where Mayank Agarwal takes it with ease. Australia are 9 down!
Full and outside off, Hazlewood drives it towards gully.
Length and on off, Josh plays it off the back foot.
Shortish and around middle, blocked.
FOUR! Gloriously driven! Full and outside off, Hazlewood opens his arms and drives it through covers for a boundary. These are useful runs for Australia.
Length and on off, kept out off the back foot.
Full and on off, driven straight down to the bowler.
SIX! That's slogged! Slower ball well outside off, Cummins backs away and slogs it way high and over the fence at long on for a biggie.
Length and on off, pushed to the leg side by Cummins.
Full and straight on off, driven towards mid off where a fumble allows the batsman to take a couple of runs.
Length and down leg, Cummins looks to play the short arm jab but ends up missing it altogether.
Good length and on middle, it is played back to the bowler. Josh was backing up there but Siraj didn't throw the ball. If he had a shy and if he had hit, he would've got Josh there.
Beaten! Length and on off, Hazlewood tries to guide it to the third man region but fails in the end. The ball goes past the outside edge.
Short of length and around off, Josh plays it uppshly towards third man for a single.
Length and on off, Cummins hops inside his crease and defends it out to the off side.
WDE! A bumper on off, too high to make Cummins play at it. The square leg umpires gives it a wide.
Full and on off, Cummins lofts it uppishly towards long off where the fielder takes it on the bounce. A single taken.
BEATEN! Length and wide outside off, Hazlewood backs away as he goes for the wild swing but misses it as the ball goes past his outside edge.
Full and on off, driven straight down the ground towards mid off this time by Hazlewood.
Short of good length around off, Cummins pulls it to mid-wicket for no run.
Length and on middle, Cummins pushes it with soft hands towards slips. The ball goes on the bounce to Rohit Sharma.
A mix up but all safe in the end. Length ball around off, pushed to covers as Cummins takes the single. He looks to take the second but is sent back as the throw comes to the bowler's end.
FOUR! Class shot! Full and on off, Hazlewood drives it through covers and gets the boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mohammed Siraj gets his maiden 5-wicket haul. What a moment and series to get. Bowls a short one around off, Hazlewood tries to uppercut it but ends up slicing it towards third man where Shardul Thakur who had 4 wickets to his name takes the catch to help his partner get to a 5-wicket haul. AUSTRALIA BOWLED OUT FOR 294 RUNS!
Shortish and around off to begin from Starc. Rohit stsys back to block.
Shortish and just outside off, Rohit keeps it out.
Fuller and wider outside off, Rohit lets it go to the keeper.
Another one outside off, angling away. Rohit makes another leave.
FOUR! Shot! Glorious shot from Rohit to get underway! Full and wide outside off, Rohit leans into the shot and creams it through the cover region. It raced to the fence.
Fullish and around off, Rohit is solid in defense.
Back of a length and around off and middle, Gill pushes it towards mid on.
Fuller and just outside off, moving away. Gill offers no shot.
Length and around off, Gill blocks it to the mid on region off the back foot.
Length ball around off, pushed towards mid on.
Length and around off, Gill watches it carefully as the balls goes past he off pole and into the mitts of Paine.
A length ball around middle and leg, Gill tucks it towards mid on calmly.
A back of a length ball around off and middle to begin from Cummins. Rohit works it towards short leg.
Length ball around off, pushed towards mid off.
Good length and just outside off, Rohit is solid in defense.
Around off on a length, Rohit blocks it nicely.
Shortish and around off, pushed towards point.

First run on the morning! This one keeps a little low. A length ball just outside off, Rohit looks to defend but the ball keeps low. The ball goes off the inner half and goes on the leg side. They cross for a single.
Good length and around off and middle, pushed towards mid on.
Shortish and around off, Rohit pushes it to the left of point fielder and calls for a quick single.
Length ball just outside off, Gill punches it straight to the cover fielder.

Gill is up and running too! Shortish and outside off, he forces it in the gap between point and gully. The gully fielder gives it a chase and returns the ball to the keeper. By that time, Gill takes two.
This time Gill will take three. Full ball on the pads, he flicks it through mid-wicket. This time the deep square leg fielder does the mop up work. Three taken.
Shortish and around off, Rohit defends it towards mid on.
Length and around off, Gill just clips it towards the square leg region and takes a couple now.
Fuller and around off, Gill drives it handsomely but for no runs as it goes straight to the mid off fielder.
Length and around off, Gill defends it towards covers this time.
Another length delivery on off, Gill blocks it back to the bowler off the back foot.
Slightly shortish and on off, Gill punches it through covers and takes a single on offer.
First signs of variable bounce there. Length and coming in sharply into Sharma. Rohit looks to tuck it to the leg side but is beaten on the pace as the ball goes off his pads to the slip region.
Length and around off, Gill pushes it back to the bowler now.
Good length and around off, Gill defends it compactly towards covers.
On a fuller length and around off, Gill once again finds the mid off fielder with his drive.
A short one on off, Gill pulls it off the back foot towards deep mid-wicket for a comfortable three runs. He has been really comfortable off the back foot in this series.

A muted appeal but aborted soon. Length and around off, Rohit looks to defend it out off the front foot but is beaten to get rapped high on the pads. Hazlewood appeals but aborts it quickly. height might be the issue there.
Length and on off, defended solidly by Rohit.
Cummins charges in to bowl to Gill as he lands on a length and on off, Gill keeps it out off the back foot.
BEATEN! That's the length Australia need to hit consistently. Short of good length around off, Gill looking to play off the back foot gets beaten on the outside edge this time.
Length and on middle, Gill pushes it to the leg side off the back foot.
Length and on off, kept out from within the crease to the off side.
Another short of good length delivery on off from Cummins, Gill pushes it off the back foot towards mid on.
Another shortish delivery on off, Gill is solid off the back foot as he plays it to mid on.
Length and around off, Rohit plays it towards mid-wicket and takes a single to get off strike.
Good length and around off, Gill is deep inside his crease as he defends it out to covers.
Short of good length on off, Gill stands tall and keeps it out towards the off side once again.
Length and on middle and leg, Gill plays it to mid on off the back foot.
Length and outside off, Gill shoulders arms to it this time around.
Slightly fuller and on off, Gill is solid in his front foot defense.
Good length and around off, Rohit plays it with a full face of the bat towards mid on.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Perfect line, perfect length and Paine does the rest. Paine's decision to start with Cummins pays off as he gets the breakthrough that Australia needed to get into the act. Beautifully bowled by Pat there, he lands one on a length and around off,Â  gets it to shape away from the right-hander. As has been the issue with Sharma that he fails to negotiate the moving ball. He once again goes to have a feel for it as his outside edge is found and Paine behind the stumps dives to his right and takes it in front of the first slip. India jolted early in their pursuit of 328 runs.
Nice line again! Pujara covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Good leave! Close leave! Cummins goes wide of the crease and angles the ball in from outside off. Pujara though trusts the bounce and shoulders arms.
Length and outside off, comes back in again but Pujara has no problem leaving that alone.
Slightly short and around off, Pujara stays on his back foot to block. End of a successful over for Australia.

A slight excitement but aborted the appeal. Length and around middle and leg, Gill looks to flick it to the leg side but is beaten to get hit on the pads. The bowler appeals but cuts soon as it might be drifting down leg.
Length and outside off, left alone there.
Short of good length on middle, clipped towards mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Slashed! Short and wide outside off, Gill brings out the square cut in play as he cuts it through point and fetches a boundary.
Length and on off, pushed back to the bowler this time.
Short of good length and around off, Gill punches it to cover-point this time to see off the over.
Length and outside off, Pujara has nothing doing with it as he leaves it for Paine there.
Cummins is bowling wide off the crease there. Bowls a length ball angled into Pujara, Cheteshwar plays it to point and looks for a run but nothing there.
Another length ball on off, Pujara can only defend it out to the off side this time.
Length and around off, Pujara plays this with soft hands towards mid on. Still waiting to get off the mark here is Pujara.
Cummins tests Pujara with a sharp bouncer, Cheteshwar ducks under it.
Length and outside off, Puajra is aware of his off pole as he makes a leave there.
Full and drifting on the pads, Gill flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for an easy three runs.
Length and on off, Pujara plays it to covers.
Full and on middle, Pujara flicks it but cannot beat the man at mid on this time.
Length and outside off, Pujara lets it be this time.
Another length delivery outside off,Â  Pujara comes on the front foot as he makes a leave.
Length and slightly closer to off, still not enough to make the batsman play as Pujara lets it go through to the keeper.
Good length and on off, Gill blocks it solidly off the back foot towards covers.
Slightly full on off, Gill defends it out once again.
Full and on off, Gill drives but Pat Cummins intercepts it in his followthrough.
Shorter and on off, Gill does not play at it as he sits under it.
Fuller and around off, blocked off the front foot this time towards mid on.
Full and on off, Gill straight drives it once again but Cummins is smart to field it in his followthrough.
Fuller and on off and middle, Pujara pushes it to mid on now.
Good length and outside off, Pujara lifts his bat and allows the ball to pass through.
Another length and on middle, Pujara clips it towards the leg side. Still waiting for his first run in this innings.
On a length and on off, Pujara solidly blocks it out off the front foot.
Another instance of the batsman missing his flick. Length and on middle and leg, Pujara goes for the flick shot but is beaten to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls to the off side there.
A bumper to end the over as Pujara ducks it.
Full and outside off, Gill shoulders arms to it.
Fuller and on off, Gill blocks it out off his back foot.

Length and on off, Gill drives it crisply wide of mid off but Wade there dives to his leftÂ  and saves a certain boundary. Gill took off for a single as Wade recovered to has a shy at the striker's end but misses it as Pujara dives to make his crease.
Full and on off, Pujara looks to play the off drive but it goes off the inner half towards square leg. A couple taken to get off the mark. A bit edgy there.
Length and outside off, left alone by Pujra.
Length and around off, Pujara watchfully plays it out to covers.
Short of good length on off, Gill punches it off the back foot towards point.
Fuller and on off, Gill drives it off the inner half of the bat to mid on.
FOUR! Gloriously driven! That should ease the nerves there. Full and around off, Gill leans into the drive and creams it through covers to get a boundary despite a diving effort from Labuschagne.
Length and outside off, Gill leaves it. The ball nipped a long way there.
Short of good length and on off, Gill punches it on the up through cover-point for three runs there.
Outside off, left alone by Pujara. An hour of play done.
Short of good length, Gill plays it off the back foot to point.
Good length well outside off, Gill does not play at it as it is not in his playing zone.
Full and angled into the pads, Gill clips it through mid-wicket and gets a single on offer.
Another length ball outside off, Pujara does not offer a shot to it.
Length and angled in on middle, Pujara fends it away towards backward square leg.
Full and on off, Pujara looks to defend it off the front foot but the ball goes off the inisde edge towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, Gill pushes it to mid off.
Tossed up, turning in to Gill, Shubhman plays it to mid-wicket.
Floated on off, pushed off the front foot towards the off side.
Flatter and on off, Gill pulls it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted around off, Pujara defends it off the front foot towards point.

NOT OUT! Umpire's Call on hitting the wickets. Brilliant from Lyon in his first over. Bowls a tossed up delivery around off, spins into Pujara. Cheteshwar comes on the front foot and pads it away. As he has been doing it the entire series against Lyon. Nathan goes up in appeal straightaway as Paine too joins in and signals 'T'. Replays come in. As no shot was offered we directly get to Ball Tracker. No shot means the impact would not have mattered as we see where the ball is heading. That is marginal as it is umpire's call on hitting the wickets. Pujara is saved as Australians look a bit disappointed there.
Shortish and just outside off, Gill punches it wide of the man at mid off for a single.
Good length and around off, blocked.
Fuller and outside off left alone.
Length and around off, poked towards the off side.
Short bouncer and just around off, Pujara sways away.
Fuller and around off, solidly kept out.
FOUR! Cheeky! Tossed up on middle and leg, Gill clips it past short leg and the ball goes past the short fine leg fielder and into the fence behind for a boundary
Tossed up on off, pushed to the bowler.
Flatter and around off, blocked.
Lands around middle, turns in. Gill lets it be.
Full and outside off, Gill comes down the track and drives but finds the cover fielder.
Loopy and around off, pushed towards the bowler.
Full and outside off, left alone by Pujara now.
Fuller and on middle, Pujara is compact as he defend it out off the front foot.
Pujara gets three now. Full and on off, Pujara drives it through covers as Lyon runs after it and manages to keep the ball in play as Wade backs him up. Good fielding and good running too.
On off, kept out off the back foot by Gill.
Length and around off, Gill plays it straight to mid off now.
Full and around off, Gill blocks it out to covers off the front foot.
Floated on middle, flicked towards mid-wicket for a single by Pujara.
Tossed up on middle. Gill plays it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on middle, whipped straight to mid-wicket by Gill.
Floated on off, defended off the front foot by Gill.
Floated just outside off, Gill pushes it to the left of mid off for a single.
Flatter and around middle, Pujara flicks but ends up hitting the short leg fielder. A dot as the ball goes towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Sweet timing from Gill. It is not that short but it is a little wide outside off. Gill punches it through cover-point and it races to the fence. 50 up for the Indians.
Length ball around off, worked on the leg side for one.
In the channel outside off, slightly fuller. Pujara shoulders arms.
Full and just outside off, pushed towards covers.
Short ball but outside off. Left alone.
Good length and around middle, kept out.
Flat but down the leg side. Gill lets it be.
Floated around off, Gill comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Stays back this time and blocks the flatter one around off towards mid on.
Shortish and around off, punched to the man at mid off.
Short and just outside off, Gill plays it towards point.
Around off, pushed to mid on. A maiden from Lyon.
Just outside off on a good length, left alone.
Landed around off on a length, blocked.
Fuller and just outside off, Pujara is not keen as he shoulders arms.
Good length and around middle, pushed to mid on.
Another one outside off, Pujara lets it be.
Bangs the last one short and it is around off and middle, Pujara sways away from the line.
Flat and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Another flatter ball around middle and leg, Gill keeps it out.
Shortish and turning in, Gill stays back to block.
Floated around off pushed to long on for a single.
Flighted around off, Pujara comes down the track and whips it to the left of mid on who dives that side to stop the ball.
Floated just outside off, kept out.
Length and around middle, pushed to mid on by Gill.
Fuller and on off, pushed to covers off the back foot.
Good length and around off, Gill stands tall and blocks it out off the back foot.

Full and on middle, Gill clips it to wide mid on and takes off for a single. The fielder from mid on gets to the ball and scores a direct hit at the keeper's end but Pujara dives to make his crease. He is safe.
On off, kept out by Pujara from within the crease.
Length and just outside off, Pujara does not want to play at it.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Too full around off, Gill drives it through covers for a boundary. Moves to 47 with that.
Full on off, driven to long on for a single.
Tossed up on middle, clipped to mid on.
Lopped up outside off, Pujara looks to pad it away but the ball turns just a touch to go behind.
On off, poked towards point.
Flatter and around off Pujara comes down the track and looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half and goes towards the leg side.

FIFTY FOR GILL! A fine knock from the youngster so far. He saw his opening partner depart early but he has kept things flowing for the Indians. He gets the milestone by punching the short ball outside off through cover-point. A huge round of applause for the young man. His 2nd half ton in Tests. Can he convert this one into a three-figure score here?
Landed around off on a length, kept out.
Shot! Full and on middle, Gill flicks it past the man at mid on who gives it a chase and stops it near the fence. Not before Gill takes three though.
Good length and around off, Pujara blocks it nicely.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Banged short and on middle, Pujara sits under it.
On the pads, Gill pads it away.
Another one down the leg side. Gill lets it be.
Flatter and around middle, kept out.
Shortish and just around off, punched straight to the cover fielder.
Floated around off, Gill blocks off his front foot.
Darted on the pad, Gill pads it away.
Ouch! Banged short and on middle, Pujara ducks but this one doesn't get up as much as Pujara thought. Gets hit on the shoulder.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid on.
Landed around off on a length, blocked.
Good leave! That wasn't too far from the off pole. This one is pitched outside off. It comes back in as Pujara lets it go to the keeper. Trusted the bounce there.
This one is an easy leave as it is wide outside off.
Very full and around off, blocked.
Looped on the pads, padded away by Gill.
Looped up and outside off, pushed to mid off.
Full and just aroudn off, Gill goes for the sweep. Nails it but finds square leg.
Flicked straight to Wade. He is looking in some pain. Flat and around off, Gill goes back and flicks it hard. The ball bounces in front of the short leg fielder and then hits him near the chest.
Tossed up on middle, clipped towards mid-wicket for a couple of runs. 50-run stand is also up between these two.
On off, blocked.
Good length and around off, Pujara pokes it towards point.
Landed around off on a good length, kept out.
Extra bounce! This one pitches around off on a good length, it bounces extra but Pujara does well to get on his toes and blocks.
Cummins goes full and Pujara pushes it to mid on. Calls for two straightaway and Gill respinds to make it in the end.

That's on the helmet. Banged short and on middle, Pujara drops his hands and looks to get out of the way. But he is late in doing so and the ball hits him on the back of the helmet. Signals Lyon that he is fine who enquires on him.
Banged short again from Cummins and Pujara this time does well to move out of the way. Good testing over from Cummins.
On the pads and Gill is happy to pad it away.
Flatter and around middle, turned on the leg side.
Floated around off, watchfully blocked.
Another one down the leg side. Gill lets it be.
Loopy ball around off, kept out.
Tossed up and around middle, turns in as Gill lets it be. Maiden over from Lyon.
Landed on a length and around off, blocked.
Good length and around off, Pujara defends it towards mid on.
Another good bouncer from Cummins. It is aimed right at the body. Pujara ducks. Again the ball kisses the helmet and goes to Paine.

Appeal for caught behind but turned down. No review from the Aussies. It is the short ball that is troubling Pujara. It is just around off and middle, Pujara looks to duck but this time he is late in moving out. Pujara takes his eyes off too. He didnd't drop his gloves this time around. The ball goes past his gloves into the mitts of Paine who takes the catch and appeals. Not out says the umpire. Terrific from Cummins here.
Shortish and around middle, blocked this time.
Shortish and just outside off, Pujara moves out of the way this time. A terrific over.
A short one down leg, Gill sits under it.
Short of good length, Gill punches it to covers this tme.
A short one on middle, pulled towards deep square leg for a single by Gill.
A short of good length outside off, It does not bounce as Pujara would have liked as he is beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length ball around off, Pujara hops and keeps it out to the off side.
Another short of good length on off, Pujara is right behind the line as he defends it down the track.
Short one on off, Gill pulls it but is well short of the fielder there. A single taken.
BEATEN! Length and around middle, Pujara looks to defend it but is beaten as the ball goes to hit him high on the pads.
Full and on off, pushed to short cover this time.
FOUR! BYES! That's beaten all for the fence. Short one on off, Pujara does not play at it. Paine too leaps but it goes well over him too and into the fence at third man for four byes.
Short and around middle, Pujara looks to fend it away but takes the blow onto his ribs this time.
On off and middle, kept out. Australia looking for a wicket with just few minutes left for Lunch.
A short one for Gill, Shubhman does well to not go after it.
SIX! Clobbered! Gill takes the short ball on. Short and outside off, Gill slaps it over backward point and over the fence there for a biggie.
Short and on middle, Gill pulls it but not off the middle of the bat. The ball goes to fine leg for a single.
Short of good length and around off, Pujara blocks it off the back foot.
After a barrage of short balls comes the fuller one around off, Pujara pushes it to mid off.

Huge appea for a catch down the leg side. Paine takes the catch and goes up in an appeal but nothing from the umpire. Another short ball around middle and leg, Pujara looks to fend it away as he takes the bottom hand off the handle. The ball brushes his shirt and goes towards Paine who takes the catch and appeal but nothing from the umpire. They think of reviewing it but opted against it in the end. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 5!
Short and down leg from Cummins to start a fresh session, Gill does not play at it.
Another short one on middle, it bounces a tad extra as Paine leaps and gloves it. Gill just watched it go over him. Cummins oversteps! NO BALL CALLED!
Short and on middle, pulled towards fine leg by Gill for a single.
Good length and around middle, it is pushed to mid on.
Fullish and around middle, pushed to mid on again. Wanted a single but opted against it.
Another length ball. It is around off and middle, Pujara is solid in defense.
A dot! Good first over from Cummins after Lunch. The last ball is shortish and around off, Pujara works it towards mid-wicket off his back foot.
Shortish and just around off, Gill punches it towards point.
FOUR! BANG! Short and outside off, Gill picks the length early and whacks it through wide mid on for a boundary.

In the air but away! Short ball again from Starc and Gill once again takes it on. Goes for the pull. It is not off the middle of the bat. He though manages to clear the man at deep square leg. Lucky for Gill as he gets two more. He would've had his heart in his mouth.
Another bumper but this time Gill sways away.
Takes on the short ball this time and helps it down to fine leg via a pull.
Pujara takes a single! Yes, you read that right. Shortish and just around off, Pujara pokes it towards point and takes a run. He gets a run after 23 balls.
Short ball on middle and leg, Pujara ducks.
Shortish and on middle, Pujara tucks it through square leg and takes two more. Good, aggressive running from Pujara.
Length and around middle, bounces a bit extra. Pujara does well to defend as he takes the hand off the handle.
Shortish and around off, pushed to mid on.
Fullish and around off, turned towards mid on again.
Good length and around off, watchfully blocked by Pujara.
Short ball down the leg side. Gill wanted to play at it but left it alone at the last moment.
Short again, Gill works it in front of square leg for a single.
Landed around off, kept out.
FOUR! Intent from Pujara. Short and wide outside off, Pujara slams the cut through the covers and finds the fence. First boundary for Pujara. 100 up for the visitors.
Back to blocking the ball as he stays in the crease to defend this short ball back to the bowler.
Short ball down the leg side. Goes way over Pujara who moves away.
Cummins continues banging it short. Gill sits under it.
Short again and Gill sits under it again.
And again! Looks like Gill has changed his plan here. Cummins bends his back again and lands this effort ball short and on middle and leg. Gill now seems to be happy ducking under it.
WOW! What was that! Cummins goes full and wide, Gill lets it be. The ball lands and then takes off. Paine collects it over his head.
Another short one. This is down the leg side. And Gill is not playing at it now. Kept watching the ball all the way though.

Another bouncer and again down the leg side. This time Paine fails to collect the ball to his left. The ball hits his gloves and goes to fine leg. They take two byes. Another barrage of short stuff from Cummins but Gill this time around has change of plans.
Shortish and around off, Pujara fends it away towards short fine leg. The ball took off a touch after hitting the deck.
Back of a length and around off, poked towards the cover fielder.
Shortish but outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Up and over! Short and wide outside off, Pujara slashes it over backward point and finds the fence. Pounced on the chance.
Shortish and around middle, Pujara is right behind the line of the ball to block.
Superb bouncer! This is around off but Pujara does really well to drop his wrists and let it go to Paine.
A length ball around off and middle, Gill pushes it towards mid on and takes a quick single.
Around off on a length, defended.
Another one on the body! A short ball around middle and leg, Pujara looks to duck under it but this one doesn't rise enough. He gets a blow on his shoulder this time.
Shortish and around middle, Pujara tucks it towards short fine leg.
Fuller and around off, watchfully defended.
Short ball down the leg side. Pujara is not interested. Another testing over ticked off.
Shortish and around middle, flicked towards mid-wicket.

SIX! BOOM! Gill takes on the short ball and deposits it way over deep square leg for a massive biggie. What a strike from Gill. Short and on middle, Gill swivels and nails the pull over deep square leg for half a dozen. He moves to 80. Just sensational from the young man.
FOUR! Up and over again! Another short ball. This one is outside off, Gill waits for it and then ramps it over short third man. One bounce and into the fence.

FOUR! BANG! This is sensational from Gill. Three in a row! A short ball and around middle, Gill moves inside the crease and nails the pull through mid-wicket. Starc, the quickest Aussie on the turf is getting hammered here. To make the matter worse, the third umpire calls it a no ball. 100-run stand comes up between these two.
Good length and on the pads, flicked to fine leg for one.
Down the leg side. Pujara lets it be. Wanted to flick it looked but opted against it in the end.

FOUR! Pujara's turn to smash Starc now. 20 from the over. A massive one. Another short ball from Starc and it is outside off, Pujara hammers it over backward point to find the fence. He says to Gill, if you can do it, I shall do it as well. Exceptional batting.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid on.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Length ball on middle, clipped through mid-wicket for a single. Gill moves to 90. 200 more needed for India.
Full and around off, blocked.
Around off on a length, Pujara is solid in defense.
Fuller and around off, Pujara plays it back to Josh.
Flatter and around off, Gill tucks it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Floated around off, Pujara is down the track to block.
Flatter and on middle, Pujara flicks it through square leg. They run three.
Fuller and around off, kept out by Gill.
Flat and around off, Gill stays back to block. Did well to keep it down in front of the short leg fielder.

OUT! TAKEN! Lyon strikes! Inspired bowling change from Paine. A very sharp catch from Smith. Heartbreak for Gill as he falls in the 90s. Lyon tosses it up and bowls it outside off, nice loop and drift. Gill looks to drive away from his body. A thick outside edge flies to the left of Smith at first slip. He is alert there as he reacts quickly and gobbles it nicely. A fine, fine knock from the youngster.
BEATEN! Length and around off, Pujara hangs his bat out but is lucky to not edge that one behind.

Ouch! That is a nasty blow! That would have pinged him hard. Short of good length and on off, this one rares from the pitch as he looks to defend. Pujara looks to fend it away but the ball hits him on the glove. He immediately threw his bat away as he grimaces in pain.
Length and around off, Pujara blocks it off the back foot.
Length and down leg, Pujara lets it be.
Full and on off, driven straight to covers.
Length and outside off, Pujara lets it be. A testing over from Hazlewood comes to an end.
Full on off, whipped towards long on for a single.
Full and on off, whipped towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, driven back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, kept out off the front foot by Pujara.
Tossed up on off, Pujara comes on the front foot but offers pad to it.

NOT OUT! GOING OVER THE STUMPS! Tossed up around off, Pujara comes down the track to defend but is rapped on the pads. There is an appeal and the umpire does not give in. Paine after pondering over a review and then takes it. Replays roll in and as Pujara is not playing a shot Ball Tracker comes in. It is missing the stumps. Pujara survives.
FOUR! Nicely done! First boundary for the skipper. Short ball around middle and leg, Rahane swivels and pulls it through short fine leg for a boundary.
Length ball around middle, clipped straight to the short leg fielder.
Fullish and outside off, kept out.
Good length and around off, Rahane pokes it between point and gully. A quick single.

Ouch! That's on the helmet! Oh dear! That was a well-directed bouncer. Pujara looks okay though. He wanted to stay away but this one came back in sharply. Pujara was once again late in moving out of the way. And gets pinged on the helmet.
No! Not a short ball. It is around off on a good length, Pujara is solid in defense.
Flatter and just outside off, poked on the off side.

Massive Spin! That landed on a rough and spun into Rahane who does not have any idea of how to play at it. Tossed up and outside off, The ball spins into Rahane who is on the back foot to play but the ball goes onto hit him on the pads. That was going down the leg. This should interest Lyon a bit more.
Flatter and around middle, clipped through mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up and around off, kept out off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, clipped to the leg side.
Tossed up and outside off, Pujara pads it away.
SHOT! Fuller and wide outside off, Rahane creams the drive through the covers. Lyon chases it down and flicks the ball back in. But they run four. Excellent running.
Fullish and outside off, it is poked towards point for a quick single.
EDGY FOUR! Lucky runs! A short ball, Pujara looks to duck away but this one doesn't rise. It takes his bat and goes over the slip cordon and into the third man fence.
Fullish and around off, blocked towards the cover region.
Shortish and around off, Pujara is right behind the line of the ball to block.
Fuller and around off, Pujara blocks nicely.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Rahane tucks it to the leg side.
Floated on middle, kept out off the back foot.
Flatter around off, Rahane punches it towards wide mid off for a single.
Fuller and on off clipped towards mid on this time.
Darted on middle, Pujara whips it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Pujara starting to open up now. Flatter and spinning into Pujara, Cheteshwar pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Length and on off, defended off the back foot.
Fuller and on off, clipped towards mid-wicket for a couple by Rahane.
BEATEN! Rahane goes for an expansive drive on this length ball outside off, gets beaten on the outside edge.
Play and a miss! Second time he gets beaten. Length ball around off, Rahane looks to play it off the back foot but the ball bounces a bit extra to beat the outside edge of Rahane's bat once again.
Fuller and on off, pushed through to cover-point for a single.
Short of good length around off, Pujara stands on the back foot to defend it.

SIX! WOW! TAKE THAT! What a strike from Rahane! The Indian skipper doesn't want Lyon to get settled here. Lyon tosses this one up and Rahane jumps out of his crease to pump it way over the mid-wicket fence.
Tossed up on off, punched off the back foot towards covers for a single.

Huge appeal! Not from all the Aussie players though. Certainly not from the bowler. Not out says the umpire. Tossed up and around offf, Pujara comes down the track and looks to work it on the leg side but he misses to get hit on the pad. The ball lobs towards short mid-wicket. The fielder takes the catch and appeals. A loud on from him, keeper and Labuschagne at short leg. Not out from the umpire. No review from the Aussies.
Fuller and around off, kept out.
On middle, Pujara manags to push it back to the bowler.
Good stop from Lyon! A fuller one around off, Pujara hits it to the right of Lyon who dives that side to stop the ball.
Length and around off, Rahane tucks it to fine leg for a single.
Fuler and on off, Pujara keeps it out.
Short one on middle, Pujara ducks under it.
Full and on off, punched through covers and gets three runs does Pujara.

OUT! CAUGHT! Rahane goes! Australians are elated! They have bounced back in the last few overs. In the last over he was beaten on the outside edge twice but this time he goes. A back of a length ball around off, Rahane arches back and looks to help it over to third man. He though ends up getting a glove and the ball is caught by Paine behind the wicket. 150th catch for Paine. 161 needed for India to win.
Good length and just outside off, Pant pokes it towards Green at gully who tumbles to his left to stop the ball. End of a successful over from Cummins.
Flatter on off, Pujara pushes it off the back foot.
Tossed up on leg, Pujara tucks it towards square leg for a couple of runs.
Tossed up on midlde, Pujara clips it past short leg.
Fuller on middle, clipped towards short mid-wicket.
Floated around off, tucked towards sqaure leg.
FOUR! Pujara helps it on its way. Flatter and on middle, pulled towards fine leg for a boundary.
Length and on off Pant pushes it to the off side.
Fuller and on off, Pant keeps it out off the front foot.

There goes Pant! A short ball on middle, Pant take sit on and pulls it through mid-wicket. Scampers back for the second. And with that, it is 1,000 Test runs for Pant. Quickest Indian wicket-keeper to to do so.
Short and down leg, Pant looks to pull but ends up missing it.
Short and angled across off, Pant leave it alone.
On off, kept out by Pant off the front foot.
Floated on off, clipped towards mid-wicket.
Floated on off, Pujara dead bats it on to the pitch.
Flighted on off, Pujara plays it to short leg.

Miscommunication but safe in the end. Fuller and middle, Pujara whips it towards mid-wicket and takes off for a single. Cummins at mid-wicket gets to the ball and releases the throw to the keeper. Pujara does well to make it in time before the bails come off as he puts in a dive.
Flat and around off, this time Pujara is solid in defense.
Floated and around off, Pujara defends.
Short one down leg, Pant lets it be.

FOUR! Pant gets into the act there! Though it is edgy but India will take it. Back of a length ball around off Pant pushes at it with hard hands. The ball takes the outside edge and goes through the gully region and towards third man for a boundary.
Length and on off, pushed to mid off.
Another fuller one on off, Pant plays it towards covers.
Length and targetting the stumps, Pant defends it from within the crease.
A short one on off, Pant pulls it as he takes his eyes off. The ball goes behind square on the leg side for a single.
Tossed up on off, Pant drives it through covers and gets a couple.
Floated outside off, turning away, Pant leaves it.
Floated outside off, left alone.
Flatter outside off, Pant slaps it through point for a single. 100 scored in this session so far.
Floated on off, clipped towards short mid-wicket.
Loopy on off, Pujara pushes it off the back foot towards short mid-wicket.
Length and on off, Pant pushes it to point.
Good length and around off, Pant looks to defend it out but ekes out an inside edge onto the box.
Length and on off, kept out.
Another length ball on off, Pant blocks it off the back foot towards short leg.
BEATEN! Length and angled around off, Pant hangs his bat out in defense but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length and on off, pushed to covers. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 5!
Nervous moments! Length and outside off, Pujara initially looks to leave it but ends up getting a glove as the ball rolls to the slips.
Fuller and around off, kept out.
Short but outside off, Pujara lets it be.
Shortish and around off, punched towards the cover region.
In the channel outside off, moves away far too much after pitching. Pujara lets it be.
Landed around off on a good length, Pujara is solid in defense. Maiden to start from Hazlewood.
Tossed up outside off, Pant lets it be.
Another one outside off, Pant lets it be.
Full and around off, pushed towards the cover.
Outside off, left alone again.
Flatter and around off, pushed towards the cover.
Looped up and around off, kept out by Pant. Maiden from Lyon from the other end as well.
Full and around off, Pujara drives it straight, Josh gets down to pick the ball and threatens to throw at the stumps as Pujara was charging ahead for a single.
Shortish and outside off, left alone.
Length and around middle, kept out.
Sharp bouncer outside off, left alone.
Outside off again, Pujara makes another leave.
Fuller and around off, Pujara pushes it towards the cover region. Three maidens in a row.
Darted outside off, Pant lets it go.
Loopy fuller ball around off, Pant defends.
Short and wide outside off, slapped to deep cover for one.
Catch is the shout! Didn't carry. Flat and turning in from around off, Pujara flicks. It falls just short of the man at forward short leg.
Full and on middle, flicked to square leg for nothing.
Tossed up and outside off, Pujara comes down the track and pushes it to mid on.
Good length and around off, keeps low but Pant does well to defend.
Shortish and just outside off, punched through covers for a brace.
Short ball and Pant goes for the pull. Hits it over mid-wicket and gets three. The man at fine leg has to do a lot of running.
Shortish and outside off, left alone.
Length and around off, pushed to mid off.
Short ball around off, Pujara sways away from the line of the ball.
Flat and just around off, pushed towards point.
Looped up and around middle, played to mid on.
Darted outside off, Pant lets it go to the keeper.
Tosses this one up but Pant is happy to defend again.
Fuller and around off, played back to Lyon.

FOUR BYES! Chance of stumping there but Paine fails to collect the ball. Lyon bowls a flighted ball outside off, Pant this time charges down the track and looks to go downtown. The ball through breaks away and goes behind. Paine cannot collect it to take the bails off. Smith at first slip cannot stop it either and it goes to the third men fence. Pant survies.
Good length and around off, tucked towards the leg side for one.
Good length and around off, punched towards the over region.
Wide outside off, Pant watchfully lets it be.
Edgy! A fuller ball just outside off, Pant looks to defend but the ball takes the thick outside edge and goes to gully.
Length and just outside off, pushed to the fielder at gully this time.
Landed around off on a good length, kept out.
Floated on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up and outside off, Pujara pads it away by coming down the track
Shortish and just outside off, punched towards the cover region for one.
Flat and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Big turn! Pitches on the rough or crack and went away to the slip fielder.

SIX! There goes Pant! What a strike! What a shot! The last ball spun away like a cobra there but Pant backs himself to clear any boundary. Lyon tosses it up and Pant comes down the track. Gets to the pitch and powers it over the long on fence. 200 up for India. They need 127 more. Australia need 7 wickets.
Short of good length on off, punched to deep point for a single.
FOUR! Slashed! Too short and wide from Starc. Pant cuts it through point and gets a boundary.
Fuller and on off, Pant pushes it down the track to mid on.
Shorter and on off, pulled towards mid-wicket for a single.
Length and on off, Pujara pushes it to covers for a single.
On leg, clipped to square leg by Pant for a single.
Tossed up outside off, Pant watches and leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off, slapped towards deep covers for a couple.
Flatter and just outside off, Pant plays it uppishly towards gully where Starc looks to go for the catch but the ball bounces just in front of him. A single taken.
Length and outside off, Pujara pads it away.
Length and on middle, Pujara whips it to the leg side for a single.
Outside off, left alone by Pant.
Flatter and outside off, Pujara pulls it to mid on.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR PUJARA! What a player, what a knock! He got hit on his elbow, then on his helmet. He was pinged on his fingers as well. But this man has shown some unbelievable courage, grit and concentration. He just bats and bats and bats. And here he is, at it again. Bruised, thumped, pinned and everything else but he is battling it out. Gets to the milestone by getting on the back foot and forcing this wide ball through backward point for a boundary. Superb innings. Can he take the team over the line here along with Pant? Gets to his 27th Test fifty which is also the slowest in terms of balls.
Fuller and outside off, Pujara drives it straight to the bowler who fields it and hits the stumps at the striker's end but Pujara was going no where.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and around middle, flicked to mid on.
Short and wide outside off, Pujara cuts it hard but finds point. 200th ball for Pujara.
Length and on off, Pant defends it off the back foot.
In the channel outside off, Pant lets it go to the keeper.
Landed around off, kept out off the back foot.
Shortish and around off, pushed towards the cover region this time.
Lovely bouncer this time. Pant looks to pull but misses.
Short ball around middle, Pant tucks it to his right and takes a quick single to keep the strike for the next over.
Tossed up but wide outside off, Pant lets it go to Paine.
Bowls it just around off, Pant punches it towards the cover fielder.
Lovely from Lyon this time. Lands this fuller and just around off, Pant looks to drive but misses. Lucky not to edge.
Flat and around off, played back to Lyon.
Full and just around off, Pant covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Comes down the track and looks to go big bit this time it takes the inner half and goes to long on. A single taken.
Short of length on off, Pant goes for the cut but ends up underedging towards the keeper.
Length and around off, Pant hops and keeps it out off the back foot.
Length and outside off, Pant slaps it towards sweeper cover for a single.
Length and angled on middle, Pujara looks to tuck it to the leg side but ends up getting an inside edge onto the pads.

A huge shout from Starc a desperate one though but the umpire does not entertain it. A fuller length ball angled onto the pads of Pujara, Cheteshwar goes for the flick but is rapped on the pads. Starc puts in a desperate appeal but nothing from the umpire.
FOUR LEG BYES! Length and down leg, Pujara looks to tickle it fine but ends up getting it off his pads to the fine leg fence for a boundary. Leg byes given.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one darted outside off, Pant lets it go again.
Floated on middle, played back to Lyon.
On middle, kept out by Pant again.
Wide outside off from Lyon. Pant doesn't go after it again. It bounces extra as it goes to Paine.
Floated around off, Pant defends.
Length and going down leg, Pujara goes for the flick but misses it altogether.
Full on off, defended to mid on off the front foot.
BEATEN! Nearly gone! Short of length on off, Pujara looks to cut it upishly but is beaten on the outside edge.
Length and on off, blocked off the front foot towards mid on once again.
101 runs needed for a win! Full and on the pads, clipped towards mid-wicket for a comfortable three runs.
Length and around off, Pant blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, clipped to wide mid on for a single. 100 needed for India to win.
Tossed up on off, played to point this time.
Flaoted outside off, left alone by Pant.
Fuller and on off, Pant dead bats it onto the pitch.
Floated and outside off, Pant shoulders arms to it. It was very close to the off pole.
On off, pushed down the track for a dot.
Fuller length ball outside off, Pujara makes a leave.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call on hitting the wickets and Pujara has to go. The second new ball has done the trick for Cummins and Australia. A superb ball from the number 1 bowler in the world. He pitches this around off and it jags back in. Pujara looks to defend but misses to get rapped on the pads. They all appeal and the finger goes up. Pujara calls for the review. Let's see what the replays have to show! Doesn't look like any bat says the third umpire. Nothing on RTS either. Time for the Ball Tracker. Umpire's call on hitting the wickets. The mighty Pujara has been removed by the Aussies. What an innings from him though.
Beaten first ball. Lovely from Cummins again. A length ball just around off, Mayank feels for it and has a poke but misses.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
SHOT! Full and around off, Agarwal pushes it down the ground and gets a brace.

Two more! A fuller ball around off, Agarwal pokes it down the ground. Cummins gets down to his right and tries to stop but misses. Two taken before the fielder from ring can collect it. End of a successful over.
Length and down leg, Pant goes for the flick but fails to get wood on the ball.
Length and around off, Pant plays with an angled bat towards point.
FOUR BYES! Some shape into the batsman. Length ball on leg, shapes away further down leg as Pant misses his flick. Paine fails to collect as the ball goes to the fine leg fence.
FOUR! Firmly driven! Full and on off, Pant drives it through covers and manages to get a boundary.
Sensible! Taps the next bell around off and takes a quick run.

Huge LBW appeal but turned down! They do not go for the review. A length ball around off, Agarwal looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pad. They appeal but not out says the umpire. A small conference from the Aussies but they opt against the review. Replays show there was a bat involved.
Length and on off, Pant drives but finds mid off.
Fuller and on off, Pant punches it through mid off for a couple of runs.
Length and angled across, Pant makes a leave now.
FOUR! Dispatched! Fuller and on off, Pant drives it through covers and gets another boundary. He is so quick to get the bat down in time and strokes it cleanly.
Length and angled on middle, clipped to mid-wicket for a single.
BEATEN! Length and outside off, Agarwal offers the bat as he plays away from the body but is lucky to not have edged that to the keeper or the slip cordon.
Full on off, driven back to the bowler.
Outside off, Pant comfortably leaves it.
Length and outside off once again, Pant does not go after it. Hazlewood oversteps! NO BALL CALLED!
Full and on off, Pant drives it through covers and takes a quick three runs. 250 up for India. 76 more needed for a win.
Lenggth and outside off, Agarwal looks to push it to the off side but inside edges it past short leg for a quick single.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket.

HALF TON FOR PANT! This has been a superb knock from the left-hander so far. And, as far as he is there in the middle, the Indians will feel that they are nothing but winning it. He got India close in the last game in Sydney but failed to close the deal. Pant has the chance to do so here. He gets to his 4th half ton by pushing the good length ball towards mid on.
